# OpenPresence — minimum validations

> Project-specific gates. Harness rules in other `.mdc` files still apply.

## Before any implementation

1. Read `AGENTS.md` and `.local/tasks/current.md` if present.
2. Check `docs/NEW-PROJECT-CHECKLIST.md` — **ASK** if checklist items are blank.
3. Use terms from `docs/GLOSSARY.md` only; do not invent domain language.

## Before marking work done

| Gate | Action |
|------|--------|
| Size caps | ≤80 lines/function, ≤200 lines/file, cyclomatic ≤10 |
| Tests | Run project test command; do not claim pass without output |
| Lint / typecheck | Run when tooling exists |
| Secrets | Never commit `.env`; use `.env.example` for keys |
| API changes | Update `docs/API-CONTRACT.md` before handlers |
| Security | Load `./agent-harness/resolve-rules.sh owasp auth` for auth/API work |

## Agent NEVER (this project)

- Commit `.local/` or `.cursor/` contents.
- Skip glossary/checklist when adding domain concepts.
- Add dependencies without user approval on greenfield tasks.
- Ship code in Portuguese — English only per repo policy.

## Local context

- Tasks: `.local/tasks/`
- Overrides: `.local/overrides/`
- Progress: `.local/ROADMAP.md`
